'''Rzhanaya Polyana''' ({{lang-ru|Ржаная Поляна}}) is a natural area in [[Krasnodar Krai]], [[Russia]], located not far from [[Krasnaya Polyana, Sochi, Krasnodar Krai|Krasnaya Polyana]].

Home of the [[Sliding Center Sanki]], it hosted [[bobsleigh]], [[luge]], and [[skeleton (sport)|skeleton]] events for the [[2014 Winter Olympics]] held in [[Sochi]].

==References==
*[http://www.fil-luge.org/News-Detail.155.0.html?&L=0&tx_ttnews%5Barc%5D=1&tx_ttnews%5BbackPid%5D=45&tx_ttnews%5BpL%5D=2591999&tx_ttnews%5BpS%5D=1212271200&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=10603&cHash=9ce74c2423 Bobsleigh and luge track for Sochi will be built in Rzhanaya Polyana.] at the [[Fédération Internationale de Luge de Course]] (20 May 2009 article accessed 23 September 2009.)

