{{Use Indian English|date=July 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Refimprove|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox mountain | name = Sangthang | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 6,480 | elevation_ref = | prominence = | listing = | location = [[Pithoragarh]], [[Uttarakhand]], [[India]] | range = [[Himalaya|Kumaon Himalaya]] | coordinates = | topo = | type = | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Sangthang''' is the [[Himalayas|Himalayan]] peak in [[Kumaon division|Kumaon]] Himalayas in [[Pithoragarh district]] of [[Uttarakhand]] state of [[India]].
==Location== It is situated in the easternmost part of [[Kumaon division|Kumaun]], lining [[Byans Valley]]. The peak is situated on Indo-[[Tibet]] border. The altitude of the peak is 6,480&nbsp;m. This peak is near to [[Om Parvat]] and famous Himalayan passes of [[Kuthi Valley]] pass in [[Kuthi Valley]] and [[Sin La]].
==Ascent== The peak was climbed for the first time by P.&nbsp;Dasgupta in 1968.
==See also== * [[Om Parvat]] * [[Mount Kailash]]-[[Lake Manasarovar]]
